<!DOCTYPE html><html><title>Hometown</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="/scss/main.css"><script src="https://fb.me/react-0.14.7.js"></script><script src="https://fb.me/react-dom-0.14.7.js"></script><script src="https://npmcdn.com/babel-core@5.8.38/browser.min.js"></script><script src="https://npmcdn.com/jquery@3.1.0/dist/jquery.min.js"></script><script src="https://npmcdn.com/remarkable@1.6.2/dist/remarkable.min.js"></script><body><nav><div class="grid"><div class="row"><div class="grid-1-1"><a href="#" class="titling type-300 pink">Hometown</a></div></div></div></nav><h1>{%= name %} {%= badge(&quot;fury&quot;) %}</h1><blockquote>
<p>{%= description %}</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Useful for protecting tokens, like templates in HTML, from being mutated when the string is transformed in some way, like from a formatter/beautifier.</p>
<p><strong>Example without <code>preserve</code></strong></p>
<p>Let&#39;s say you want to use <a href="https://github.com/beautify-web/js-beautify">js-beautify</a> on a string of html with Lo-Dash/Underscore templates, such as: <code>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;%= name %&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</code>:</p>
<p>js-beautify will render the template unusable (and apply incorrect formatting because of the unfamiliar syntax from the Lo-Dash template):</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;%=n ame %&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Example with <code>preserve</code></strong></p>
<p>Correct.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;%= name %&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>For the record, this is just a random example, I&#39;ve had very few issues with js-beautify in general. But with or without js-beautify, this kind of token mangling does happen sometimes when you use formatters, beautifiers or similar tools.</p>
